<subSubSection id="C37D654AFFF44724DF42C41CFB9E7C71" pageId="12" pageNumber="1408" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD836C1FFF44724DF42C41CFB9E7C71" blockId="12.[827,1443,1626,1801]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1408">
<emphasis id="B913EAD3FFF44724DF42C41CFC0F7D17" box="[827,954,1626,1647]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1408">Etymology:</emphasis>
Named in reference to the fabled animal from Chinese mythology, Qilin or Kirin (
<emphasis id="B913EAD3FFF44724D96BC43DFAF17DF6" bold="true" box="[1298,1348,1659,1678]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1408">DZDz</emphasis>
). It was a chimeric creature that combined the traits of several animals and is a general allusion to the fierce and enigmatic habitus of the species. The specific epithet is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D654AFFF44725DF42C574FDC57DCF" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1409" pageId="12" pageNumber="1408" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD836C1FFF44725DF42C574FDC57DCF" blockId="12.[827,1443,1842,1894]" lastBlockId="13.[145,761,1574,1719]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1409" pageId="12" pageNumber="1408">
<emphasis id="B913EAD3FFF44724DF42C574FC077C3F" box="[827,946,1842,1863]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1408">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Scape short, about twice as long as pedicel; pretarsal claws of all legs bidentate; fore wing vein Rs+M longer than 2Rs; second and third submarginal cells equal in length; 1rs-m meeting Rs slightly after r-rs; 2rs-m complete and tubular; second discal cell short (about twice as long as wide); hind wing with five hamuli; metasoma with cylindrical gaster.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF186649FFF54725DCE8C722FE4C7EAA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6458557" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6458557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6458557/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1409" startId="13.[145,225,1380,1402]" targetBox="[148,763,198,1336]" targetPageId="13">
